### 1.5 Anti-Patent Covenant & Prior Art

By accessing, using, or obtaining a copy of this Software, you agree to the following:

#### 1.5.1 Definitions for This Section

-   **"You"** includes you personally, and (if applicable) your employer, your affiliates, parent companies, subsidiaries, successors, assigns, contractors, and any entity under common control with you.
-   **"Covered Invention"** means any invention, method, process, algorithm, technique, system, design, data structure, or user interface that is disclosed in, derived from, implemented by, or substantially similar to any portion of this Software's source code, documentation, architecture, or output.

#### 1.5.2 Covenant Not to File Patents

You agree that **you will not**, directly or indirectly:
1.  File any patent application, in any jurisdiction, claiming any Covered Invention.
2.  Acquire, purchase, or accept assignment of any patent or patent application that claims a Covered Invention.
3.  Encourage, assist, fund, or induce any third party to file, acquire, or assert any patent claiming a Covered Invention.

This covenant applies **retroactively** to any patent applications filed after the first public release date of this Software, and **perpetually** into the future.

#### 1.5.3 Anti-Assignment & Anti-Circumvention

To prevent circumvention of this covenant:
1.  You shall not assign, transfer, license, or sell any patent or patent application claiming a Covered Invention to any third party (including shell companies, holding entities, or patent assertion entities) for the purpose of enforcing such patent against the Author or any user of this Software.
2.  Any such transfer shall be deemed a material breach and shall not release you from liability under this covenant.
3.  Any patent obtained in violation of this section shall be subject to the automatic grant-back in Â§1.5.4.

#### 1.5.4 Grant-Back of Patent Rights

If you (or any party defined in "You" above) obtain any patent that covers any Covered Invention, you hereby grant, automatically and irrevocably:
-   To the **Author**: A perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free, fully paid-up, non-exclusive, irrevocable, sublicensable license to use, make, have made, sell, offer for sale, import, and otherwise exploit the patented invention in connection with any software, hardware, or service.
-   To **all other licensees** of this Software: The same license as above.

This grant-back is automatic upon issuance of any such patent and requires no further action by any party.

#### 1.5.5 Acknowledgement of Prior Art

1.  You acknowledge that the public release date of this Software (as evidenced by its version control history, public release records, or any timestamped public archive) constitutes **prior art** under applicable patent law in all jurisdictions.
2.  You agree that any patent application filed after such date that claims Covered Inventions disclosed herein is likely invalid due to lack of novelty.
3.  You agree not to challenge, dispute, or contest the status of this Software as prior art in any patent proceeding.

#### 1.5.6 Breach & Remedies

1.  Any violation of this Anti-Patent Covenant constitutes a **material breach**, immediately and automatically terminating all rights granted to you under this entire license.
2.  Upon breach, you shall immediately cease all use of the Software and destroy all copies in your possession.
3.  The Author shall be entitled to seek **injunctive relief** (including temporary, preliminary, and permanent injunctions), **actual damages**, **statutory damages**, **attorneys' fees**, and **any other legal or equitable remedies** available under applicable law.
4.  The Author's right to seek remedies is **not waived** by any delay in enforcement.

#### 1.5.7 Survival

The obligations and covenants in this Section 1.5 (Anti-Patent Covenant & Prior Art) **survive** any termination, expiration, or revocation of this license. Your agreement not to file patents, and the grant-back provisions, continue in perpetuity even if you no longer use the Software.

