### 2.2 Broad Definition of Commercial Use

For the purposes of this license, **"Commercial Use"** is defined broadly to include any activity where the Software is used to generate revenue, support revenue-generating activities, or provide a competitive advantage. This explicitly includes:

| Category | Examples |
|---|---|
| **Direct Sale** | Selling, renting, or leasing the Software or any product incorporating it. |
| **SaaS / Network Services** | Operating the Software (or a derivative) on a server to provide a service, API, or web application to any user (paid or free). |
| **Internal Business Tools** | Using the Software within a for-profit organization for internal business operations, R&D, automation, or employee tooling. |
| **Freelance/Contract Work** | Using the Software in any deliverable for a client or as part of paid contract work. |
| **Advertising Revenue** | Distributing the Software alongside advertisements or as part of a freemium model. |
| **Sponsorships/Donations** | Operating the Software in a context where you receive donations, tips, or sponsorships. |
| **Competitive Advantage** | Using the Software to gain a market or business advantage over competitors. |

